Hungarian Stocks Fall Most in a Week, Led by Mol, OTP, Telekom

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-03-23T13:48:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/hungarian-stocks-fall-most-in-a-week-led-by-mol-otp-telekom.html
Hungary’s benchmark BUX stock index
retreated the most in a week, led by Mol Nyrt., the country’s
biggest oil refiner, OTP Bank Nyrt., the largest lender, and
Magyar Telekom Nyrt., the biggest phone operator.  The BUX gauge of 12 companies fell as much as 1.3 percent,
its biggest intraday retreat since March 16, and traded down 1
percent at 22,297.69 as of 2:25 p.m. in Budapest.  Mol, which has a 33 percent weighting in the BUX index,
tumbled 2.7 percent to 23,050 forint, heading for its biggest
one-day drop in 1 1/2 months. Nearly 57,000 shares changed
hands, or 37 percent of the three-month daily average.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
